Interface IField

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IInstruction
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDecimalField
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteVectorCopy, ByteVectorDefault, ByteVectorDelta, ByteVectorNoOp, ByteVectorTail, ConstantInstruction, CopyBase, DecimalCopy, DecimalDefault, DecimalDelta, DecimalField, DecimalIndividualOperators, DecimalNoOp, DefaultBase, DeltaBase, DeltaBytesBase, FastField, IncrementBase, Int32Copy, Int32Default, Int32Increment, Int32NoOp, Int64Copy, Int64Default, Int64Increment, Int64NoOp, IntegerDelta, RuntimeInstruction, StringAsciiCopy, StringAsciiDefault, StringAsciiDelta, StringAsciiNoOp, StringAsciiTail, StringUnicodeDelta, TailBase, TemplateIDInstruction, Uint32Copy, Uint32Default, Uint32Increment, Uint32NoOp, Uint64Copy, Uint64Default, Uint64Increment, Uint64NoOp, UnicodeCopy, UnicodeDefault, UnicodeNoOp, UnicodeTail

    public interface IField
extends IInstruction
    A FAST scalar field - ie an integer, decimal, asciiString, etc. This excludes groups and sequences although they are defined as "fields" in the FAST spec.

    • Method Detail

      • getDictionaryName

        IName getDictionaryName()
        Dictionary name as identified by FAST dictionaryAttr, after translation of special "template" and "type" names.

        Note that the name returned is an IName, which means that a namespace may be specified. This will happen if the name was translated from "template" or "type", since templates and types are both identified by namespace aware names.

        This is the dictionary that will apply to the field. It can be inherited. "The dictionary name is specified by the dictionary attribute on the field operator element or where allowed by the schema on ancestor elements. If there are more than one dictionary attribute in the ancestry, the attribute of the nearest element applies. If the attribute is not specified, the global dictionary is used."

        This may return null if no dictionary is specified or inherited.

        Returns:
        Name of applicable dictionary

      • getDictionaryType

        int getDictionaryType()
        Dictionary type as identified by FAST dictionaryAttr.

        Can be unknown, global, template, type or user.

        Returns:
        int constant from Constants indicating the type.

      • getDictionary

        IDictionary getDictionary()
        Dictionary instance associated with dictionary name.

        The dictionary instance identified using the field's dictionaryName and the fields context within its template.

        Returns:
        IDictionary associated with this field. None if field has no operator which requires a dictionary.
        See Also:
        getDictionaryName()

      • getInternalKey

        short getInternalKey()
        Internal small int key used to look up dictionary values.

        This is computed and assigned to each field when the template is processed.

        It only needs to be unique for this field's dictionary - not unique across all fields.

        Returns:
        internal dictionary key, -1 if undefined.

      • getKey

        IName getKey()
        FAST nsKey - defaults to name of field as returned by getName.

        This is used to select dictionary values.

        Returns:
        IName of key (id field is never used).

      • getName

        IName getName()
        FAST nsName.

        In the FIX world, the id attribute of the returned IName will match the FIX tag of this field.

        Returns:
        IName identifying field.

      • getValue

        IValue getValue()
        FAST initialValueAttr

        This is used in some operators. For example it is used to specify the constant value for the constant operator and the initial value for the delta operator if there is no previous value defined.

        Returns:
        Initial value or null if not defined.

      • isAssignedPresenceBit

        boolean isAssignedPresenceBit()
        True if this field has a bit assigned in the presence map.

        The logic for this is not intuitive. It is described in the FAST specification in the section on PresenceMap's.

        For example:

        • Mandatory fields with a constant operator or no operator do not have a presence bit.
        • Optional fields with no operator do not have a presence bit (they *always* appear in the encoded stream with decoded absence indicated by a NULL value).
        • Fields with delta operators do not have a presence bit.
        Returns:
        True if this field has a bit assigned in the presence map.

      • isOptional

        boolean isOptional()
        FAST presenceAttr - mandatory or optional.
        Returns:
        boolean True if optional
